Chinese Vice Premier Sun Chunlan (left) and Czech President Miloš Zeman (middle) at the event Photo: Yin Yeping/GTDuring the visit of Czech President Miloš Zeman for the second Belt and Road Forum for International Cooperation, the Czech Embassy in China held a reception to celebrate the 70th anniversary of diplomatic relations between China and the Czech Republic on April 25. Some 500 people attended the event. Czech President Miloš Zeman and Chinese Vice Premier Sun Chunlan made a speech on the occasion. The newly appointed Czech Ambassador to China Vladimír Tomšík delivered a welcome speech at the beginning of the reception. During the event, some documents were also signed for cultural cooperation and exchanges on both sides. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Delegation of HUST attends alumni gala in Los AngelesChinese driving Vegas growthHaving fun